attribute_information.alternateIdentifier: An identifier other than the primary Identifier applied to the resource being registered. This may be any alphanumeric string which is unique within its domain of issue.
attribute_information.contributor: The institution or person responsible for collecting, managing, distributing, or otherwise contributing to the development of the resource. To supply multiple contributors, repeat this property.
attribute_information.creator: The main researchers involved in producing the data, or the authors of the publication, in priority order. For instruments this is the manufacturer or developer of the instrument. To supply multiple creators, repeat this property.
attribute_information.date: Different dates relevant to the work.
attribute_information.description: All additional information that does not fit in any of the other categories. May be used for technical information or detailed information associated with a scientific instrument.
attribute_information.fundingReference: Information about financial support (funding) for the resource being registered.
attribute_information.geoLocation: Spatial region or named place where the data was gathered or about which the data is focused.
attribute_information.identifier: A DOI (Digital Object Identifier) registered by a DataCite Member.
attribute_information.language: The primary language of the resource.
attribute_information.publicationYear: The year when the data was or will be made publicly available.
attribute_information.publisher: The name of the entity that holds, archives, publishes, prints, distributes, releases, issues, or produces the resource. This property will be used to formulate the citation, so consider the prominence of the role.
attribute_information.relatedIdentifier: Identifiers of related resources. These must be globally unique identifiers.
attribute_information.relatedItem: Information about a resource related to the one being registered.
attribute_information.rights: Any rights information for this resource.
attribute_information.size: Size (e.g., bytes, pages, inches, etc.) or duration (extent), e.g., hours, minutes, days, etc., of a resource.
attribute_information.subject: Subject, keyword, classification code, or key phrase describing the resource.
attribute_information.title: A name or title by which a resource is known. May be the title of a dataset or the name of a piece of software or an instrument.
attribute_information.version: The version number of the resource.

relationType.IsCompiledBy: B is used to compile or create A
relationType.IsContinuedBy: A is continued by the work B
relationType.IsDerivedFrom: B is a source upon which A is based
relationType.IsIdenticalTo: A is identical to B, for use when there is a need to register two separate instances of the same resource
relationType.IsMetadataFor: additional metadata A for a resource B
relationType.IsNewVersionOf: A is a new edition of B, where the new edition has been modified or updated
relationType.IsOriginalFormOf: A is the original form of B
relationType.IsPartOf: A is a portion of B; may be used for elements of a series
relationType.IsPreviousVersionOf: A is a previous edition of B
relationType.IsPublishedIn: A is published inside B, but is independent of other things published inside of B
relationType.IsReferencedBy: A is used as a source of information by B
relationType.IsSourceOf: A is a source upon which B is based
relationType.IsSupplementTo: A is a supplement to B

relationType.References: B is used as a source of information for A
relationType.Reviews: A is a review of B
